title: United Airlines engine fire over the Pacific 90 minutes into a flight from Honolulu
text:
United Airlines engine fire over the Pacific 90 minutes into a flight from Honolulu   
Oct 18, 2015 eTN   
A Boeing 767-400ER operated as United Airlines flight 144 departed Honolulu, Hawaii at 4.25pm on Saturday for a 10 hour non stop domestic flight from Honolulu, Hawaii to Washington DC Dulles International Airport in Virginia. The twin engine Boeing 767 long-range, wide-body jet landed back to Honolulu about 3 1/2 hours later. 
The reason: A fire was reported from one of the engines about 1 1/2 hours into the flight over the Pacific Ocean. 
The plane landed safely and all passengers left the airliner and took off about 4 hours later. 
A reason for the fire is not yet known. United Airlines was unable to be reached.
